news.title: UK house prices post biggest quarterly drop since 2009: Halifax
news.para: The average house price fell 1.5% month-on-month in December, following a 2.4% fall in November and marking the fourth consecutive monthly decline, Halifax said.

news.title: CBI books Unitech, former directors in fresh bank fraud case of Rs 395 crore
news.para: The company was allegedly enjoying a vendor bill discounting (VBD) facility, a kind of credit, of Rs 400 crore from the IDBI bank in 2012, the officials said.

news.title: Sobha's sales bookings rise 36% to Rs 1,425 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Sobha Ltd achieved highest-ever quarterly sales bookings in the December quarter in terms of both volume and value. The average price realisation improved to Rs 9,650 per square feet, up 21.9 per cent from the corresponding quarter of last year.

news.title: Macrotech Developers' sales bookings up 16% to Rs 3,035 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Macrotech Developers informed that the company has achieved its "best-ever Q3 (October-December) pre-sales performance of Rs 3,035 crore showing a growth of 16 per cent on a YoY basis."

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to auction 140 properties
news.para: ​​Bids will be opened from 10.15 am the same day. A total of 49 freehold residential units and 91 leasehold commercial properties are up for auction.

news.title: Shortage of raw materials pinches construction sector in Mysuru, Chamarajanagar
news.para: Around one ton of M sand is being sold for Rs 1,500, which was earlier available at Rs 1,100 about 45 days ago. Similarly, the price of a brick has increased from Rs 7 per piece to Rs 12 this year.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 21 crore property tax from defaulters in 15 days
news.para: NMC has set a target of Rs 150 crore for the property tax department in the current fiscal and the collection so far is Rs 134 crore. NMC had collected the property tax amounting to Rs 110 crore by the same time last year.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: Online auction of plots fetch Rs 23 crore for VMRDA
news.para: ​Two plots in Kanapaka layout in Vizianagaram made the most as these attracted bids for 48,500 and 45,200 respectively against the upset price fixed by the VMRDA at 20,000.

news.title: L&T Realty Developers to sell its entire stake in Think Tower Developers
news.para: "L&T Realty Developers Ltd, a wholly owned subsidiary of Larsen & Toubro Ltd, has entered into an agreement to sell its entire stake of 99 per cent in Think Tower Developers Private Ltd, a subsidiary company (TTDPL), on January 5," Larsen and Toubro (L&T) said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Merge old & new property IDs by January 8: ULB to Gurugram civic body
news.para: Varshney directed that data integration of the old and new property IDs be done by January 8, since chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar will review the status of the work on January 10.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC tells RWAs to go to government before court
news.para: An HC division bench comprising Justice Harinder Singh Sidhu and Justice Lalit Batra passed these orders while disposing of a plea filed by Corporate Green Buyers Welfare Association against the DLF regarding a housing project in Gurgaon.

news.title: Mumbai-based builder had roped in another firm in Rs 27 crore cheating case
news.para: Developer Jagdish Ahuja was detained and brought from Punjab to Mumbai on December 16, by the city EOW. He was arrested in a Rs 27 crore cheating case for allegedly duping several flat buyers.

news.title: Father-son duo dupe man of Rs 10 crore in builder scam in Mumbai
news.para: Complainant Mukesh Agarwal who is a real estate consultant and also deals into logistics, lodged an FIR with the Borivli police on January 2.

news.title: Yashasvi Group buys Navkar Institute building in Ahmedabad
news.para: Ahmedabad-based Yashasvi Group has purchased the Navkar Institute building. Its promotor, Jigar Bharwad, confirmed the deal but refused to share details of the deal size.

news.title: Maharashtra: 78 property registration officials under government lens
news.para: Of the 78 officials listed, 44 are from Pune, 23 from Thane, eight from Aurangabad and three are from Latur. Latest data available with the department showed that 13,920 property documents from Pune, Thane, Aurangabad, and Latur were under the scanner.
